description: Having both better efficiency and sturdyness than the Skirmish type, these well-rounded wings are often used by adventurers and raiders who can afford their cost and maintenance.

name: Stiletto Walker Wings Rugged
description: Being made from a specially coated cloth, Rugged wings are known to go through entire wars without a need for replacement.

name: Stiletto Walker Wings Skirmish
description: Providing comparable efficiency to medium-sized wings while being slightly more sturdy than the base ones, Skirmish wings are useful when you don't know what to expect on your travels.

name: Stiletto Walker Wings Small
description: Mesmerizing to watch as they catch the wind, these intricate wings boast more power and efficiency than standard wings. Their horizontal, low profile design make them smaller targets for incoming projectiles, and at the same time allow nomads to shoot over them.

name: Stinger
description: Small Ballista for remote control while steering. Needs to be reloaded manually.

name: Stomping Station
description: Basic crafting station simulates the blunt force of a foot to crush vegetables and soft minerals. An important tool for nomads who must always keep their feet in top condition.

name: Stone Axe
description: Nearly all nomads are expert carpenters, and the hatchet is essential to their way of life.

name: Stone Humidifier
description: When placed in a base and filled with water and charcoal, this ingenious contraption slowly releases a mist that  keeps you hydrated over time. Its efficiency depends on the number of Nomads gathered around it.

name: Structure Hardening Base Module
description: Stacking this module increases the health of the whole base.

name: Strut
description: Ancient technology scavenged from the waste. No one is sure what they were used for in the past, but crafty Nomads can use them at ancient fabricators to construct modules which can be installed in Walkers to give them special abilties.

name: Sturdy Grappling Hook
description: Sturdy grappling hook

name: Sulfur
description: A yellow mineral that typically forms in sulfur lakes.
whereToFarm: Mined from sulfur rocks or collected from mutated mushroom gases.

name: Sulfur Bomb
description: Ammo for sling or catapult. Releases a short duration sulfur cloud on impact that deals health as well as corrosive durability damage.

name: Sunset headdress
description: Fiberwork crown used in the most illustrious Flotilla social ceremonials.

name: Super Cluster Bomb
description: Ammo for sling or catapult. Spawns dozens of tiny explosions covering a large surface area. Very effective at disrupting walkers and nomads on the ground.

name: Swampwood Galoshes
description: Developed by the secretive Swampwood tribe, these rubber boots protect Nomads from the painful sting of toxic water.

name: Table
description: Decorative furniture that also allows to place objects on it.

name: Tablet
description: Carved images of animals can be felt on this tablet.
whereToFarm: Crafted in Ancient Fabricators found in the most difficult Oases.

name: Tall Stinger
description: A Small Ballista placed on a raised arm that lets the driver get better firing angles.

name: Tallow
description: Animal fat rendered down into a non-perishable liquid,  used to lubricate rotating components and as an alternative fuel source.
whereToFarm: Can be rendered using a purification station.

name: Tar
description: Thick liquid used in heavy and complex constructions. Ignitable in combination with other materials.

name: Thornberry
description: Grows inside a notoriously dangerous, bulbous plant. The thornberry has mystical properties and is said to have appeared with the arrival of Nibiru.
whereToFarm: Grows inside a mutated Thornberry Cactus in wet areas.

name: Throne
description: Make your adversaries bow before this intimidating assembly of sticks and planks.

name: Throwable Aloe Bomb
description: Handheld ammunition. Covers nomads in green goo that heals them for short duration.

name: Throwable Insect Bomb
description: Handheld ammunition. a sack of angry insects sure to distract and confuse enemies while disabling their movement.

name: Throwable Smoke Bomb
description: Handheld ammunition. Can create a smokescreen reducing vision in the area.

name: Throwing Net
description: A portable net with a release mechanism that allows to throw it by hand.

name: Throwstone
description: Either a fantastically aerodynamic stone, its form perfected for best throwing experience... Or just a sharp chip of rock that you can throw at someone in a pinch.

name: Thumper
description: At some point in their sunny life, every Nomad finds out that in some situations blasting a bunch of projectiles at the problem solves it faster than one could say "cactus". Uses Throwstones as ammo..

name: Tied keffiyeh scarf
description: Used by nomads as protection from the burning sun and the all-present sand.

description: An iconic walker distinguished by tiered design and open, flat deck spaces. Dozens of large weapons can be stationed on it, but without a crew it's not very defensible.

name: Titan Walker Legs
description: These versatile legs can step over fissures, climb rocky mountains, and ford fast flowing rivers. While not very protected, they're light and cheap to construct.

name: Titan Walker Legs Armored
description: Armored legs that easily deflect simple projectiles.

name: Titan Walker Legs Heavy
description: Made of strong, heavy logs that are expensive to produce but provide unbeatable protection.

name: Titan Walker Wings Heavy
description: Large and heavy cloth of the heavy wings can withstand more intense battles than any other type.

name: Titan Walker Wings Large
description: Generates the highest possible physical force for walker movement. Very complicated to construct due to their size.

name: Torch
description: The nomads travel where the land is always bright, but eclipses will cause periods of unexpected darkness.

name: Torque
description: Torque Consumption
whereToFarm: Generated by Windmills or Walker Wings.

name: Torque Backpack
description: Enables nomads to transport torque between various devices. The belt also significantly increases the effectiveness of grappling hooks.

name: Torque Battery
description: Stores torque by winding up a mechanism with a rope inside.
whereToFarm: Crafted in Character Crafting. Stores torque.

description: Produces torque while the walker is moving. Hold SHIFT to consume torque on a walker, or use it to power advanced crafting stations.

name: Toxic Remains
description: The leftovers of a shamanic ritual.

name: Trap Door
description: Opens automatically when a nomad steps on it. Deadly in combination with other traps, like spikes.

name: Travellerâ€™s Staff
description: While nomads no longer travel on foot to make their migration across the world, there exists a deep affection for the old ways. The tradition of converting walking staffs for battle has yet to die.

name: Treasure Map
description: The faded ink and worn paper hint at a long-abandoned civilization, with cryptic symbols and markings pointing the way to a hidden oasis or buried treasure. Brave explorers who can decipher the map's secrets and navigate the unforgiving desert terrain will be rewarded with valuable relics and a glimpse into the mysteries of a bygone era.

name: Tree Sap
description: Lifeblood of the Redwood trees, this sticky substance is valued by flotillan alchemists for its adhesive properties.

name: Trip Wire Trap
description: Triggers a small explosion when a nomad steps on the tripwire.

name: Triple Stitch Armor
description: A secret weaving technique creates surprisingly strong armor with no loss in meanueverability.

name: Triple Stitch Boots
description: A secret weaving technique creates surprisingly strong armor with no loss in meanueverability.

name: Triple Stitch Bracers
description: A secret weaving technique creates surprisingly strong armor with no loss in meanueverability.

name: Triple Stitch Fabric
description: A tightly woven cloth that is hard to cut and nearly waterproof. The Flotillan standard.

name: Tube Spade
description: [Use from Inventory or Quick Slots] Used for harvesting resources from the soil. Long ago, Nomads invented it as the simplest and most efficient way of digging in the ground while traveling.

name: Tusker Walker
description: Enough deck space for both large weapons and the crew needed to operate them. The tusker walker is a juggernaut when it comes to hauling space, and is primarily used by rich traders that need to transport tons of valuable goods. Slow and hard to maneuver, it's often escorted by swift combat walkers. Owners of tusker walkers rarely fail to get a return on their investment.

name: Tusker Walker Wings

Slow and unmaneuverable, it's often escorted by swift combat walkers. Owners of cargo walkers rarely fail to get a return on their investment.

description: Said to induce hallucinations that can reveal ancient wisdom. Grants Nomad the ancient wisdom to build a Walker.

name: Vitamins
description: Creation of Vitamins, enhancing your abilities

name: Walker Climber
description: A buildable attachement that helps yank nomads onto a walker's deck for quick and easy boarding.

name: Walker Packing Compartment
description: Enables walker to pack other walkers into special compartments attached to the hull.

name: Walker Totem
description: Decorate your surroundings with this undeniable pinnacle of rupu ingenuity and artistry.

name: Walkers
description: Walkers and Upgrades

name: Wall
description: Above average strength, can be packed on walkers.

name: Wall 1
description: Average strength, can be packed on walkers.

name: Wanderer's Potion
description: Forget everything you know about yourself. Resets stats of your character and returns all points.

name: Water Bed
description: Luxurious bed with a huge water container to hold the most amount of respawns possible.

name: Water Circulator
description: This insulating suit traps excreted fluids and recycles them with state-of-the-art worm technology.

name: Water Condenser
description: Collects moisture from the air and stores it as clean water. Efficiency depends on the area where the condenser is built.

name: Water Storage - Tier 1 Upgrade
description: Water allows you to respawn and to travel to other oases. Try and keep your water storage filled - running out of water during combat means certain defeat.

name: Water Storage - Tier 2 Upgrade

description: Stacking this module decreases the water cost of travelling.

name: Weapons Strongbox
description: Weapons seized from pirates by the Flotilla. May contain various types and quantities of weapons.

name: Weightless Walker Module
description: Stacking this module decreases the weight of a packed base.

name: Windmill
description: Harnesses wind to generate torque automatically. A torque battery is required to transfer the torque between devices.

name: Winged Helmet
description: A helmet which provides superior filtration of particulates.

name: Wingsuit
description: Nomads are accustomed to leaving their fate to the winds. While some Nomads have managed to stay airborn for long periods of time and can perform nimble landings, many drop like a leaf.

name: Wood
description: This versatile material is the focus of Flotillan engineering. Produces ash and charcoal when burnt.
whereToFarm: Found as driftwood on the ground or by chopping trees.

name: Wood Log
description: Manufactured at a lumber mill.

name: Wood Shaft
description: The Rupu are skilled imitators, and can crudely reproduce human fighting techniques and constructions. They use wood shafts to prop up their mud huts, giving them a striking resemblance to the Nomads' walkers.
whereToFarm: Often wielded by Rupu as a weapon.

name: Wooden Dart
description: Ammo for Stingers and Repeater.  Weak and crude, best suited for hunting Phemke and unarmored Nomads.

name: Wooden Gear
description: A large wooden gear made out of primitive materials. Used as the base rotational axis for mid-sized walkers.
whereToFarm: Can be found scattered throughout the oasis or crafted at an Advanced Woodworking Station.

name: Wooden Rod
description: Roughly sharpened pieces of Walker wrecks, fashioned by the Rupu into crude bolts and used as ammo for Ballista.

name: Wooden Slab
description: A crude wooden briquette, used in construction and as a better fuel source. Burns cleanly to ash.

name: Woodworking Station
description: Basic crafting station cuts wood into basic parts.

name: Worm Fang
description: A trophy of tremendous value proving the ultimate hunting skills and heroism among Nomads. Exchange for valuable rewards!
whereToFarm: Very rare drop extracted from the interior mandible of the Worm.

name: Worm Sand
description: Appearing in the sands roamed by the Old Ones - giant worms of the desert, this substance has strange properties affecting both living creatures and mechanical constructions in ways that affect the energy inside them.
whereToFarm: Excavated from red sands near worm sightings.

name: Worm Scale
description: The corpse of a single worm can provide enough meat to feed a large family for months; its hard scales can be used to craft armor; its silk makes the sturdiest sails, its sinew the strongest rope; and its blood, when imbibed, heightens the userâ€™s olfactory senses to supernatural levels.

name: Worm Silk
description: Worm silk exists in vastly different tensile strengths and purities, and must be graded by the Flotillan Merchant's Guild before it can be legally sold at markets. Aside from certain prohibited substances, it is one of the most desirable luxury goods.
whereToFarm: Excreted by live worms or found fossilized on some trees.

name: Worm Tincture
description: An extremely potent essence of worm secretion that grants Nomads vivid memoirs of the events long forgotten. Drinking grants +10 attack attribute points until death.

name: Worshipping Wreath
description: Decorate your surroundings with this impressive object of fervent devotion.

name: Wrapped keffiyeh scarf
description: Used by nomads as protection from the burning sun and the all-present sand.

name: Wreath
description: Make your adversaries bow before this intimidating assembly of sticks and planks.

description: Flotillan scholars claim that the Wyndan tribe has roots as a prominent civilization that existed long before the apocalypse.

name: Wyndan Flame Sword
description: The Wyndan tribe is said to have pioneered the first walkers.

name: Wyndan Warhammer

name: Wyndanblade Quarterstaff
description: Long ago, the Wyndan tribe mediated a lasting peace between the plains people. Today, they serve the Guardians as peacekeepers and engineers.

name: Zirconium Metal
description: this metal gleams with a silvery hue, hinting at its unique properties. Lightweight yet strong, zirconium is essential for crafting more durable weapons, and protective gear that can withstand the harsher environments of the desert. Its rarity makes it a coveted resource among nomadic clans, often leading to fierce battles over small quantities.
whereToFarm: Often found in Rupu hordes as you traverse the most ancient sites known to the Floatilla
